# ChkTeX configuration
# Docs: man chktex
#
# Note: this file MERGES with the system /etc/texmf/chktex/chktexrc, it does
# not replace it. The system rc already wipes \input, \cite, \ref, \label,
# \pageref, \cite, \nocite, \index, \graphicspath, etc., so we only need to
# add project-specific commands.
#
# Warning suppression is done via -n N flags in the Makefile, not here.
# `Silent { ... }` and `WipeArg { ... }` lists take *command names*, not
# warning numbers, despite the misleading name of `Silent`.

# Wipe arguments of project-specific commands so chktex does not lint
# their contents (e.g. as if they were prose).
WipeArg
{
    \addbibresource:{}
}
